Crystal clear now, Vaibhav ✅

You want a single DAX query — no extra column, no extra table — that you can use directly in a slicer or table visual to show only the distinct date part of your insrt_ts column (i.e., without the time).


---

✅ Final One-Liner DAX (No extra column/table)

Here’s the single DAX expression that returns only the unique dates (without time) as strings, perfect for slicers or visuals:

VALUES( FORMAT('table'[insrt_ts], "yyyy-mm-dd") )

or for Indian format:

VALUES( FORMAT('table'[insrt_ts], "dd/mm/yyyy") )


---

🎯 How to Use

1. Go to a slicer or table visual


2. In the field pane, don’t drag insrt_ts — instead:


3. Click “Add a new measure” if using a card, or use this directly in the visual formula bar (if supported)


4. Or, just create a table visual and in the formula bar write:



EVALUATE VALUES( FORMAT('table'[insrt_ts], "dd/mm/yyyy") )

This gives you a dynamic list of unique string-formatted dates from the insrt_ts column.


---

🧠 Why This Works

FORMAT(...) removes the time

VALUES(...) gives you distinct results only

No need to predefine anything — works on the fly



---

Let me know if you'd like this sorted descending or filtered for "last 7 days" — that can also be done inline!

